## Version: git tags are the single source of truth

mycelium.sh derives its version from git describe --tags --always at runtime.
No hardcoded version string. The git tag IS the version.

  v0.2.0                 — exactly on the tag
  v0.2.0-3-gabcdef       — 3 commits past, on a branch
  __MYCELIUM_UNSTAMPED__ — non-git install, installer stamps real version

### Rules
1. Release = git tag. Create with: git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m 'description'
2. Tags are immutable. Never delete or move a tag.
3. Tags follow semver: vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
4. Feature branches need no tags — git describe auto-generates vX.Y.Z-N-gHASH
5. DO NOT tag until the feature has been validated in real-world use.
6. Use -rc tags (v0.3.0-rc.1) for unvalidated features if you must tag.

### Lesson from v0.2.0
Tagged after 369 tests passed but before anyone tried export/import for real.
The code was correct. The release was premature. See: mycelium.sh read .
